\[
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The gradient of 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{a}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu$
\end_inset

 equals
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\nabla\gamma=\frac{1}{(1-p_{a}+\nu)^{2}}\left[\begin{array}{c}
1-p_{a}\\
\nu
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

The asymptotic variances of all 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\nu}$
\end_inset

s in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:coefficients"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 are known (Moss, 2023), as is the variance of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{p}_{a}$
\end_inset

