\begin_layout Section
Concluding remarks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are many alternatives to the 
\begin_inset Formula $\ac$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Knowledge coefficients
\series default
.
 If you buy the rationale behind the 
\begin_inset Formula $\ac$
\end_inset

, we have argued that knowledge coefficients should be prefered in its stead.
 The Brennan–Prediger coefficient is especially attractive, for several
 reasons.
 First, it closely matches Gwet's rationale behind the 
\begin_inset Formula $\ac$
\end_inset

.
 Second, it is paradox-resistant, and arguably the only paradox-resistant
 agreement coefficient.
 Finally, it is more robust than the other easily estimable knowledge coefficien
ts discussed in Moss (2023).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Using classical measures of chance-corrected agreement.
 The paradox of kappa is arguably not a paradox at all.
 For why would you expect two raters agreeing less than expected by chance
 to have a positive agreement measure? Just reporting Fleiss' kappa or Cohen's
 kappa is very reasonable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Reporting 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{a}$
\end_inset

 along with Cohen's or Fleiss' kappa.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have not considered inference for the new weighted definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\ac$
\end_inset

 when the guessing models are equal.
 This would involve an application of the delta method of slightly higher
 complexity than the other problems, as we would require the covariance
 between 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{p}_{a}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{p}_{wa}$
\end_inset

.
 This covariance can be deduced using the theory of 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

-statistics.
 Weighted inference when the guessing distributions equal the marginal distribut
ions is possible, however, as the knowledge coefficient is invariant with
 respect to weight changes.
 
\end_layout

